{"id":101,"date":"2022-03-16T23:08:06","date_gmt":"2022-03-16T23:08:06","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/atlantabitdevs.org\/?p=101"},"modified":"2022-03-23T19:54:01","modified_gmt":"2022-03-23T19:54:01","slug":"bitcoin-socratic-seminar-5","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/atlantabitdevs.org\/2022\/03\/16\/bitcoin-socratic-seminar-5\/","title":{"rendered":"Bitcoin Socratic Seminar #5"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>It&#8217;s time for the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.meetup.com\/atlantabitdevs\/events\/283224005\/\">first Atlanta BitDevs Socratic Seminar of 2022<\/a>! Come hang out with Bitcoiners and developers to discuss the latest developments in Bitcoin, Lightning, and related technology.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2>What is a Socratic Seminar?<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Inspired by other BitDevs meetups around the US, our Socratic Seminar events are formatted to foster debate, information sharing and lively discussion.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>Discussion topics are provided ahead of the event<\/li><li>The event moderator(s) leads the audience through the topics<\/li><li>Raise your hand to grab the mic and participate in the conversation<\/li><li>We go to a bar afterwards<\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<h2>Special Presentation<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"576\" src=\"https:\/\/atlantabitdevs.org\/content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/pleb-fm-leaderboard-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-103\" srcset=\"https:\/\/atlantabitdevs.org\/content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/pleb-fm-leaderboard-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/atlantabitdevs.org\/content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/pleb-fm-leaderboard-300x169.jpg 300w, https:\/\/atlantabitdevs.org\/content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/pleb-fm-leaderboard-768x432.jpg 768w, https:\/\/atlantabitdevs.org\/content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/pleb-fm-leaderboard-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/atlantabitdevs.org\/content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/pleb-fm-leaderboard-1568x882.jpg 1568w, https:\/\/atlantabitdevs.org\/content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/pleb-fm-leaderboard.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This past weekend, members of Atlanta BitDevs participated in the SatsX hackathon and took the Overall Best Prize for <strong>PlebFM<\/strong>, an auction-style jukebox where you big over the Lightning network to bump your music to the top of the queue. <a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/Cork__Screw\">Alex Lewin of NCR<\/a> will do a presentation on this project, his motivations for the idea, and what he learned from building it.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Discussion Topics<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<h3>Spook Nodes \ud83d\udc7b<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Pen-testing Lightning &#8211; using spook nodes to find unannounced channels.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https:\/\/youtu.be\/_AwXSzzc9k0?t=8\">Video<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/github.com\/BitcoinDevShop\/hidden-lightning-network\">Code<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>Whisper Addresses \ud83d\udd75\ufe0f\u200d\u2640\ufe0f<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Generating stealth addresses for private bitcoin transactions.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https:\/\/youtu.be\/_AwXSzzc9k0?t=211\">Video<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/whispervillage.org\/\">Demo<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/github.com\/ArcadeCity\/WhisperVillage\/wiki\/Whisper-Addresses\">Explanation<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/github.com\/ArcadeCity\/WhisperVillage\">Code<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>Spads \ud83c\udf86<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8220;Spontaneous Ads&#8221; are opt-in ads. Advertisers pay over Lightning to post the ad, and users are paid over Lightning in order to have the ads delivered to them. It&#8217;s sort of a cut-out-the-middle-man model.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https:\/\/youtu.be\/_AwXSzzc9k0?t=1450\">Video<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/lnspads.com\/\">Website Demo<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>Multi-path LN payment with sub-second runtime \u26a1\ufe0f<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Rene Pickhardt was able to compute a multi-path payment flow over the Lightning network in 0.65 seconds.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/renepickhardt\/status\/1501898812620685318?s=12\">Tweet<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/lists.linuxfoundation.org\/pipermail\/lightning-dev\/2022-March\/003510.html\">Mailing List Post<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>Fiat Swaps &#8211; Lightning based stablecoin \ud83d\udcb0<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Joko publishes a technique for constructing stablecoins over Lightning and Liquid.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/jokoono\/status\/1501213103714971666\">Tweet<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/github.com\/sputn1ck\/betterchivo\">Code<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>Extras \ud83c\udf89<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Last minute additions if there&#8217;s time.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4>First Tether stablecoin TX in a Lightning channel &#8211; Synonym<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/Synonym_to\/status\/1506388477268660238?s=20&amp;t=n4IL3_H-kd-YMsFcN0VNIg\">https:\/\/twitter.com\/Synonym_to\/status\/1506388477268660238?s=20&amp;t=n4IL3_H-kd-YMsFcN0VNIg<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Add support for BIP47 reusable payment codes to BDK<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/github.com\/bitcoindevkit\/bdk\/pull\/574\">https:\/\/github.com\/bitcoindevkit\/bdk\/pull\/574<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Automate Lightning Node Management with CLBOSS<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/medium.com\/blockstream\/automate-lightning-node-management-with-clboss-84be2e8a7555\">https:\/\/medium.com\/blockstream\/automate-lightning-node-management-with-clboss-84be2e8a7555<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>It&#8217;s time for the first Atlanta BitDevs Socratic Seminar of 2022! Come hang out with Bitcoiners and developers to discuss the latest developments in Bitcoin, Lightning, and related technology.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":102,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[4],"tags":[8,7,24,16,11],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site 